  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/deliveroo/672e4b05-ec90-443e-aee1-4a4d412e0096/application",
    "company": "Deliveroo",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "a9b9a6e3c7675dbf",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "SENIOR DIRECTOR, COMMERCIAL ENABLEMENT\n\nJoin us in our mission to transform the way people shop and eat — and our merchant partners sit at the heart of that mission. As we continue to scale globally across restaurants, grocery, retail, and new verticals, we’re investing in the next phase of our commercial capability. Our Commercial team sits at the centre of Deliveroo’s marketplace—shaping how we serve partners worldwide. From negotiating key partnerships to unlocking new revenue streams and crafting data-led growth strategies, we take on big challenges that move the business forward. If you thrive in fast-paced, commercial environments and want to influence the future of a global brand—this is the team for you.\n\nWe’re looking for a Senior Director, Commercial Enablement to join our London team. In this senior, high-impact leadership role reporting directly to the Chief Revenue Officer, you’ll own and elevate how our merchant-facing teams operate worldwide, setting global standards and driving adoption at scale.\n\nGet to know our Commercial https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/the-commercial-team/ team — what drives us, how we work, and what you can expect.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\nYou’ll lead a team of 40+ specialists and sit on the Merchant Leadership Team. This role exists to raise the bar across how we operate globally, bringing consistency where it matters and flexibility where it’s needed across hundreds of frontline commercial roles.\n\nHere’s what your day-to-day might look like:\n\n - Global Standard Setting: Own the commercial agenda end-to-end, defining standards for the full merchant lifecycle—from acquisition and onboarding to growth and off-boarding.\n\n - Product \u0026 Tech Partnership: Shape scalable, automated, and AI-enabled merchant-facing tools in collaboration with Product and Tech leaders to improve efficiency and commercial outcomes.\n\n - Go-to-Market Execution: Lead the rollout of merchant-facing process and technology changes, ensuring high adoption rates across diverse, matrixed commercial teams.\n\n - Scaled Engagement: Oversee B2B CRM, web, and paid channels to drive partner acquisition and engagement through evergreen merchant content.\n\n - Performance \u0026 Incentives: Design and evolve commercial reporting, metrics, and incentive structures in partnership with Data Science and Analytics to support global decision-making.\n\n - Commercial Learning: Own the L\u0026D agenda, ensuring frontline teams globally possess the frameworks and skills needed to deliver a world-class merchant experience.\n\n - Inclusive Leadership: Build and coach a high-performing enablement organisation while influencing the wider commercial population through a complex matrix structure.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED TO THRIVE\n\nOur ideal candidate will bring senior commercial leadership experience and the resilience to operate at scale in fast-moving environments:\n\n - Senior Leadership Experience: Proven track record leading large, multi-market commercial, enablement, or sales organisations, ideally within a marketplace or high-volume B2B environment.\n\n - Driving Adoption: A strong history of successfully embedding new processes, tools, and ways of working across large, geographically dispersed frontline populations.\n\n - Matrix Navigation: Experience influencing Executive-level stakeholders and senior leaders without direct authority in a highly matrixed organisation.\n\n - Data-Led Judgment: A structured, analytical approach combined with the mental agility to adapt global best practices to local, real-world contexts.\n\n - Product Fluency: Comfort partnering deeply with technical teams to shape automation and platform-led solutions.\n\n - Operational Resilience: High energy and the appetite to operate at pace within a constantly evolving, high-growth business.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters, solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n🔧 Make a visible impact every day\n\nYour work directly improves experiences for customers, partners and riders.\n\n🌱 Learn fast in an entrepreneurial environment\n\nWork close to the market with autonomy, pace and real responsibility.\n\n🧠 Build a career, not just a role\n\nStretch yourself, develop new skills and grow as the business evolves.\n\n🌎 Deliver together in an inclusive culture\n\nCollaborative, values-driven teams that support how you work best.\n\nWe aim to create a fair process that lets your skills shine—our interview typically includes 4-5 stages. Find more about how we hire here https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/how-we-hire/.\n\n\nOUR GLOBAL STRUCTURE\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\n\nDIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSION\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
